I quite like the connections to real world science history, it shows a real care for research that I think improves most kinds of writing. I like, as well, how quickly you overcome the cliche of a gun with  properties, and reveal the more significant effect, that has little to do with its function as a gun, but only could have been revealed after extensive testing of the more obvious effect. It's a nice little reminder that, in universe, the Foundation can never lose sight of the fact that if they don't understand how an anomaly works, they can't be sure they know all its properties, either.

There seems to be more of a mystery involved here, with the fragments of recovered document, and the mystery end note, but I wish I had a little more of a clue as to what that's about?







